<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870619-0120 </DOCNO><HL> General Automation Inc.To Pay $4.5 Million to IRS</HL><DD> 06/19/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> GENA TAXESINTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE (IRS) </IN><DATELINE> ANAHEIM, Calif.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   General Automation Inc. said it agreed to pay the Internal Revenue Service about $4.5 million in taxes, interest and penalties stemming from an audit of its fiscal years 1972 through 1981.    The computer products concern said it will pay $500,000 June 30 and the rest in quarterly payments over two years.    The company also said that, in conjunction with the agreement, it placed about $1 million in five-year, 8% unsecured notes with a group of private investors. The investors also received five-year warrants to buy for $6.38 a share about 110,000 shares of General Automation, which has about 5.4 million shares outstanding.    In a statement, General Automation said it &quot;believes that ongoing accruals for the obligation&quot; are &quot;adequate.&quot; </TEXT></DOC>